<br>
Wow, they were so close to taking the lead after a week or two of all those level 50s killing level 20s non stop.<br>
<br>
How nice it must be now for them to lose what? 70 points per kill they made? the 50 for the actuall kill, then the 20 or so that they had gained initially also. haha<br>
<br>
I guess they had been farming the low level people even more than I had thought. Very nice job on Verant's part. Now if they would just give melee a fighting chance again and put the cancel line back on agressive spell lists. I mean last time I checked, dragons seemed to enjoy casting strip enchantment spells on us, and I *THINK* that it isnt because they want to buff us.<br>
<br>
-L <p>Legna
55 Shadows
Rallos Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/box.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/28/01 8:50:13 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/Kambic/TRINITY.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The evils of Sullon</span><hr size=1> I think it's kinda funny heh<br>
<br>
And they DO need to fix the pumice/cancel thing<br>
