Canbik Virulentus, 40th Halfling <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse">Rogue</a> of Rallos Zek, <a href="http://www.eqrogue.com">Order of the Black Rose</a> (Retired)<br>
Joyous Mackdaddy, 23rd Human Enchanter of Sullon Zek [Test], Anarchy (Player Wiped)<br><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unimmbull.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nimmbull</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/28/01 10:38:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The evils of Sullon</span><hr size=1> I completely agree...to a point.  The evils that are just out in Kunark in complete safety and out of harm's way it's like, what's the point?  Why did you come to a PvP server?  I went to Kunark *once* to get a spell and I was so disgusted with the place I took off asap.  The Kunark Gimps are back and this time they're all evil....<br>
<br>
BUT, The evils that are staying on Antonica I am finding very very useful and good players.  Well organized and such.  Especially the ones growing up in Odus.  When you have to defend your territory on a regular basis, you get good practice at it.  I admire the Newts and Goods in the same way- they are constantly in contact with the other 2 teams.  Makes for a healthy PvP environment, and well it's fun.  I like knowing some of the tricks of the trade now...<br>
<br>
Nimm <p>Nimmbull
<br>Retired 47th Level Hoodlum, Bristlebane
<Br><A href="http://sanguineblade.8m.com"><FONT color="#ff0000" face="">Sanguine Blade </FONT></A>
<BR>Cinderheart, Sullon Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/29/01 4:33:14 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The evils of Sullon</span><hr size=1> Evil lost 30,000+ points and will probably continue to lose points from now on.  If someone kills another with over 20 levels difference, they will lose points on the first kill.  <br>
<br>
The point system is a bit messed up, so they might change it again.  If not, oh well, it just means evil won't get nerfed, ever.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umarbh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MARBH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/29/01 8:02:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The evils of Sullon</span><hr size=1> Hah, kinda funny that the person who dropped off the board was shame, a lvl 54 newt druid.  It aint just evils that were farming greenies.  Don't be so hasty with the tar and feathers.  <br>
<br>
Had a guy tell me last night, &quot;&quot;You only kill greens&quot;....which would mean I was wacking lvls 5, so I don't know what he was on.<br>
<br>
