</TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unarith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Narith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/29/01 8:31:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The evils of Sullon</span><hr size=1> Though I have yet to try cancel magic line on the other teams, it seriously counts as a non agressive spell!? &lt;sigh&gt;.<br>
<br>
As for greenies I let them pass unless they are in a higher level zone than they should be, but even then I tell them to leave the zone now and I will let them live but if they stay they are open game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utulaksz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TulakSZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/29/01 9:47:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The evils of Sullon</span><hr size=1> The point structure change is a good thing imo but will not prevent folks from farming greens. Although now for maximum points they need to be creative. Like in EF today there was a 40+ necro rooting and tapping for his lower level buddy to swoop in for killshot and points at little or no risk to themselves.<br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umordier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/30/01 12:58:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The evils of Sullon</span><hr size=1> Coming from the evil perspective, let me clue you in a bit.  I've been killed five times so far.  Four of those kills came at the hands of high high red, corpse-camping newts in WC (one of which was Bagen).  When my guild went hunting Dharma and her sidekicks they found them in LOIO, a zone they were too high to pve in, attacking high teens evils.  Shame, the lvl 50whatever newt druid fell off the charts b/c of his bottom feeding.  He STILL resorted to training my guild during a raid on Saturday hehe.<br>
<br>
Bottom line:  there was bottom feeding going on within ALL the teams, you just saw one side of it.<br>
<br>
As for the evils in Kunark...um, why wouldn't they fight there?  No zone is "safe", and the newt/good teams have a closer "home-base" zone (FV) than non-iksar evils do (OT).  And personally if I was an Iksar I'd just stay there rather than go to a continent where I'm hated in EVERY city.  <br>
<br>
I wouldn't say evils in Kunark are avoiding pvp at all.  In fact, I'd venture to say that Kunark is phaseII of pvp on Sullon Zek, followed by Velious.  Kunark will end up being a nasty war zone, especially LOIO...and if it doesn't you can only blame the newts and goods hehe, cause the evils are already there.<br>
<br>
Morvran McGuinness, Shanks<br>
